<plot>In this Thrills of Music short from Columbia, radio disc jockey spins the records that cut to Claude Thornhill and his Orchestra playing Thornhill's arrangement of Tchaiskoowsky's "Arabian Dance," and then Thornhill and his Orchestra provide the music while Fran Warren sings "A Sunday Kind of Love", and Gene Williams does "Oh, You Beautiful Doll."</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?111219</url></doc>
